  "text": "A psychological perspective on the quantified employee self is quite limited to the experience of the individual, but also in-depth in its appreciation of how emotions, thoughts/beliefs and actions inter-relate around personalized data engagement. Mathur and colleagues [CITATION_1] ) titled one of their workplace field studies 'tiny habits in the giant enterprise', emphasizing how an initial psychological need to belong to a self-quantification initiative gradually translates into forms of participation and habitual routines.",
